{"id": "duc04-testb-38:0#2", "contents": "The underlying issues driving the tension between Syria and Turkey include Turkey's accusations that Syria is sheltering Kurdish rebels, which Syria denies. Syria, in turn, accuses Turkey of forming military alliances with Israel and building dams on the Euphrates River that threaten its water supply. The Arab world has called for restraint, with editorials warning that another conflict would harm the region. Israel has stated that it does not want to become involved in the military confrontation, with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu reassuring Syria that Israel has taken steps to alleviate the tension."}
